> I want to install Chat GPT also on VS Studio but there are lots of choices. Which one should I choose based on my workflow
with you and the curent project needs?

⏺ Based on your workflow with me (Claude Code) and current project needs, here are the best options:

  Recommended: GitHub Copilot

  Why:
  - Best code completion for React/TypeScript/Next.js
  - Excellent inline suggestions while typing
  - Chat feature similar to Claude
  - Works seamlessly with existing Git workflow
  - $10/month (or free for students/open source maintainers)

  Use case: Real-time code suggestions as you type

  Alternative: Continue (Free)

  Why:
  - Works with multiple AI models (Claude, GPT-4, local models)
  - Can use your own Anthropic API key (pay per use)
  - Similar interface to Claude Code
  - Open source, highly customizable

  Use case: If you want flexibility to switch between AI models

  Not Recommended: ChatGPT extension

  Why:
  - Less integrated with coding workflow
  - Better suited for general chat, not code generation
  - Redundant with Claude Code

  ---
  My Recommendation:

  GitHub Copilot - complements Claude Code perfectly:
  - Copilot: Real-time autocomplete while you type
  - Claude Code (me): Complex tasks, refactoring, architecture decisions, debugging

  This combo gives you:
  1. Fast inline suggestions (Copilot)
  2. Deep problem-solving (Claude Code)
  3. No workflow overlap

  Install: VS Code Extensions → Search "GitHub Copilot" → Install → Sign in with GitHub

  Want me to help you set it up?

