  1. Inline autocomplete - But you dictate code, so typing speed isn't a bottleneck
  2. Tab-completion suggestions - Claude Code already does this via edits
  3. Function generation - You already get this from me

  Better FREE Alternative: VS Code IntelliSense

  Already built-in, gives you:
  - TypeScript autocomplete
  - Function signatures
  - Import suggestions
  - Works with your voice input

  ---
  My Recommendation: Skip Copilot

  Your current setup is optimal:
  - Voice input = fast code entry
  - Claude Code = intelligent problem-solving
  - IntelliSense = free autocomplete

  Save the €10/month. The value added by Copilot doesn't justify the cost in your workflow.

  If you want to experiment with AI alternatives later, try Continue (free, uses your own API keys).

