  - Can't run git push or any terminal commands
  - Just provide code suggestions you'd need to copy/paste manually

  It's basically the ChatGPT website inside VS Code - not a coding agent.

  ---
  Better FREE Alternative: Cline

  You mentioned Cline earlier - that's your solution!

  Cline CAN:
  - ✅ Edit files directly
  - ✅ Run Git commands
  - ✅ Update Memory Bank
  - ✅ Works exactly like Claude Code
  - ✅ Uses same memory-bank structure
  - ✅ FREE (uses your own API keys - pay per use)
  - ✅ Supports Claude, GPT-4, or local models

  Cost: ~$0.10-0.30 per task (only when you use it)

  ---
  Your Optimal Workflow:

  1. Primary: Claude Code (full sessions, complex work)
  2. End of session overflow: Cline (quick tasks, Memory Bank updates, commits)
  3. Skip: ChatGPT extensions (they can't do what you need)

  Cline is already installed in your VS Code (you have .clinerules in your project). You just need to:
  1. Add your Anthropic API key to Cline settings
  2. Enable subagents (per workflow-protocols.md)
  3. Use it when Claude Code session ends

