> How do I select the GPT model in Cline

⏺ In Cline, here's how to switch models:

  Method 1: Quick Switch (Recommended)

  1. Open Cline panel in VS Code (sidebar icon)
  2. Look for model dropdown at the top of the chat
  3. Click it → Select model:
    - Claude models (Anthropic API)
    - GPT-4 models (OpenAI API)
    - Or other providers

  Method 2: Settings

  1. Open VS Code Settings (Cmd+,)
  2. Search: "Cline"
  3. Find: "Cline: API Provider"
  4. Change from "Anthropic" to "OpenAI"
  5. Enter your OpenAI API key if not already set

  Model Options in Cline:

  Anthropic (when not throttled):
  - claude-sonnet-4 (best, most expensive)
  - claude-sonnet-3.5 (good balance)
  - claude-haiku (fast, cheap)

  OpenAI (backup when throttled):
  - gpt-4-turbo (best quality)
  - gpt-4 (good balance)
  - gpt-3.5-turbo (cheapest, faster)

  Cost Comparison:

  - GPT-4: ~40% cheaper than Claude Sonnet
  - GPT-3.5-turbo: ~90% cheaper (but lower quality)

  For emergencies: Use gpt-4-turbo - good quality, reasonable cost.

  You'll need an OpenAI API key if you don't have one already. Want help getting that set up?

